real_commentary: An incredible noise inside the Olympiastadion as England get the Euro 2024 final under way.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The Final is underway! Spain versus England, both teams eager to claim glory.

real_commentary: Spain are seeing a lot of the ball in these early exchanges but they're being forced back. A first touch for Luke Shaw, a first tackle which he wins.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating early with 73% possession, controlling midfield play.

real_commentary: Spain keeper Unai Simon has touched the ball more than anyone else so far.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain controlling the game early, dominating possession in their defensive third.

real_commentary: Great start for Luke Shaw. He wins another tackle. That's three out of three. Now a first corner for Spain after John Stones puts Nico Williams' hopeful cross behind.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating early, controlling midfield with 76% possession for three minutes.

real_commentary: Spain are starting to show their attacking intent. Marc Cucurella is out wide deep inside England's half but he is forced back.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain, delivered by Nico Williams. Conceded by John Stones.

real_commentary: Neat and tidy by Spain. England are yet to mount a serious attack.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating early with 96.4% possession, controlling the midfield.

real_commentary: Good defending by Kyle Walker and then Declan Rice as Nico Williams looks to pounce inside the penalty area. England look solid at the back but we've seen nothing from them in terms of an attacking threat.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 100%, controlling midfield for 2 minutes.

real_commentary: England are trying to break forward and Jude Bellingham wins a free-kick inside Spain's half after a foul by Rodri. This is in a decent position.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Even contest in midfield, both teams feeling each other out.

real_commentary: The set-piece is floated into the Spain box but there is a foul by Marc Guehi and Spain go again.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Rodrigo Hernández (Spain) on Jude Bellingham (England) near the right wing.

real_commentary: Oh, that's outstanding by John Stones. A super challenge by the England defender to thwart Nico Williams who has started really strongly. Williams looks Spain's biggest threat at the moment.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for England as Kyle Walker goes down.

real_commentary: Half a chance for Robin Le Normand but it drops well wide.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Robin Le Normand's right footed shot from the centre of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: That's more like it. Kyle Walker finds some space out wide and sends in a pass which is put behind for England's first corner.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 82%, primarily in England's defensive third.

real_commentary: England are stepping it up! Bukayo Saka is posing a threat and threads a nice pass to Declan Rice who lets fly. It's blocked. England are looking much more lively.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for England. Phil Foden delivers, conceded by Aymeric Laporte.

real_commentary: Biggest positive for England so far? Luke Shaw. He's won every challenge and is keeping Lamine Yamal very quiet.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain maintaining total control with 100% possession in their defensive third.

real_commentary: And just like that 20 minutes gone in a flash. Nothing for England to be seriously concerned about so far.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Declan Rice (England) on Daniel Olmo (Spain) in the attacking third.

real_commentary: Danger for England. Phil Foden gives the ball away just outside his own penalty area and Dani Olmo tries to tee up Lamine Yamal who cannot find the target.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Marc Cucurella (Spain) on Phil Foden (England) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: Luke Shaw looks really sharp and is getting into some decent positions. Now Harry Kane has gone in late on Fabian Ruiz and is shown a yellow card. That's England's 12th booking of the tournament - Kane has two.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Harry Kane (England) shown a yellow card for a foul on Fabián Ruiz (Spain).

real_commentary: One attempt by England. They have yet to register an attempt on target.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for England as Kobbie Mainoo goes down.

real_commentary: One attempt by England. They have yet to register an attempt on target.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Fabián Ruiz Peña (Spain) down with an injury, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: England are really struggling to carve out any chances. It's tight and cagey. Goalkeeper Unai Simon has had a really quiet final so far.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Fabián Ruiz Peña's right footed shot from the edge of the box denied by Jordan Pickford.

real_commentary: That's going to hurt! Dani Olmo's studs make contact with Declan Rice's chest and the referee whips out a yellow card.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Daniel Olmo Carvajal (Spain) receives a yellow card for a foul on Declan Rice (England).

real_commentary: That's going to hurt! Dani Olmo's studs make contact with Declan Rice's chest and the referee whips out a yellow card.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Declan Rice (England) down with an injury, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: Did anyone really expect this to be a rip-roaring end-to-end final? Right now, it feels like one goal could win it although England have played well at this tournament after going behind.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Phil Foden (England) is down, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: Did anyone really expect this to be a rip-roaring end-to-end final? Right now, it feels like one goal could win it although England have played well at this tournament after going behind.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Fabián Ruiz Peña (Spain) down with an injury, receiving medical attention.

real_commentary: Tow quick corners for Spain. The second is half cleared to Dani Olmo who lines up a shot but it's blocked. Jordan Pickford has still to be seriously tested.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 100%, controlling the midfield effectively.

real_commentary: Lamine Yamal has the ball out wide deep inside England's half. He attempts to deliver it into the box but Luke Shaw is in the right place to clear. Shaw has hardly put a foot wrong.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 73%, controlling the midfield effectively.

real_commentary: What's this? A terrific run by John Stones who drives towards the edge of Spain's penalty area before he is dispossessed.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating the midfield, controlling 70.9% possession. Spain struggling to break through.

real_commentary: A decent spell of possession by England which started with Declan Rice driving forward but it's ended when Kobbie Mainoo gives the ball away.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England in control, dominating midfield for the last two minutes. 55.6% possession. Kyle Walker leading the charge with 12 events.

real_commentary: Now Spain captain Alvaro Morata wins a corner after a good piece of defending by John Stones. It doesn't come to anything. Fair to say this hasn't been a classic.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 88.2%, controlling midfield for the last 2 minutes.

real_commentary: Strong end to the half by England. Good play by Kyle Walker before Harry Kane has an attempt blocked. Now England have a free-kick about 30 yards out.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain, delivered by Álvaro Morata. Pressure mounting as the game remains goalless.

real_commentary: Wow. Rodri has not come back out. Martín Zubimendi is on.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Harry Kane's right footed shot from the centre of the box denied by Rodrigo Hernández.

real_commentary: Who will be celebrating at the end? Here we go...back under way.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Harry Kane's right footed shot from the centre of the box denied by Rodrigo Hernández.

real_commentary: Oh, my! That's the closest England have come to scoring. The free-kick is flicked on into the path of Phil Foden who on the stretch forces Unai Simon into his first serious save.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Harry Kane's right footed shot from the centre of the box denied by Rodrigo Hernández.

real_commentary: All square. Everything to play for.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain has maintained 100% possession, dominating the game for the last two minutes.

real_commentary: First blood to Spain! England are undone 69 seconds into the second half. It's a lovely move with Lamine Yamal at the centre of it. It falls to Nico Williams free inside the box and he steers it beyond Jordan Pickford.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The second half is underway. Euro 2024 Final remains goalless.

real_commentary: First blood to Spain! England are undone 69 seconds into the second half. It's a lovely move with Lamine Yamal at the centre of it. It falls to Nico Williams free inside the box and he steers it beyond Jordan Pickford.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for Spain. Rodrigo Hernández Cascante off due to injury, replaced by Martín Zubimendi Ibáñez.

real_commentary: Almost a second for Spain! England have not turned up this half. This time a chance for Dani Olmo but he snaps at it and it goes wide.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession with 80%, controlling the defensive third effectively.

real_commentary: No panic from England just yet. They were behind in their three previous games and still managed to get through them in the end.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Daniel Olmo's left footed shot from the center of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: England have to go for it now! Still just the one attempt on target.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominant in midfield, controlling play for the last two minutes.

real_commentary: England need to find some composure. They have been rattled by that goal and now John Stones goes into the book for a late challenge.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating possession for the last three minutes, controlling the midfield effectively.

real_commentary: 12 July: Nico Williams' 22nd birthday. 13 July: Lamine Yamal's 17th birthday. 14 July: Williams scores on a Yamal assist in the Euro 2024 final.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] John Stones (England) receives a yellow card for a foul on Martín Zubimendi (Spain).

real_commentary: This doesn't look good. England are all over the place! After John Stones makes a vital clearance, Nico Williams goes for goal and it's just wide. England are giving the ball away so cheaply.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shots] Spain applying pressure with two attempts from Álvaro Morata; first blocked, second wayward.

real_commentary: There is only one team in this - and it's not England.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Nico Williams' right footed shot from the edge of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: It looks like England are about to make a change. Gareth Southgate needs to do something - it's too easy for Spain.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Álvaro Morata (Spain) on John Stones (England) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: Ollie Watkins is getting ready to come on. Is Harry Kane's final about to end?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating possession with 67.4%, primarily in their defensive third.

real_commentary: Harry Kane passes the armband to Kyle Walker before making way for Ollie Watkins. England fans respond with a roar. That's a positive change as far as they are concerned.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating the midfield with 100% possession, led by Bukayo Saka's activity.

real_commentary: That's very late! Nico Williams on Bukayo Saka and England have a free-kick out wide deep inside Spain's half. Phil Foden is going to whip this in.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Nico Williams (Spain) on Bukayo Saka (England) near the box.

real_commentary: That's another disappointing delivery. Easily cleared.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Nico Williams (Spain) on Bukayo Saka (England) near the box.

real_commentary: Oh, my. Wow. That's the best we have seen of Jude Bellingham in this final. He turns his marker on the edge of the box and creates space for himself before drilling it towards the net. Wide.
our_sequence_commentary: [Free Kick] Free kick for England after a foul on Phil Foden near the left side of the box.

real_commentary: Turn away now England fans.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating possession with 65.4%, controlling the midfield.

real_commentary: Lamine Yamal doing Lamine Yamal things. The 17-year-old creates space for himself outside the box and fires towards the net only for Jordan Pickford to push it behind. Pickford keeps England in this.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Aymeric Laporte's header from the center of the box denied by Declan Rice.

real_commentary: Spain have replaced captain Alvaro Morata with Mikel Oyarzabal.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain. Lamine Yamal delivers, conceded by John Stones. Spain maintains the pressure in an open game.

real_commentary: Another England change. Cole Palmer for Kobbie Mainoo.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for England. Cole Palmer replaces Kobbie Mainoo.

real_commentary: ICEEEEEE COLD PALMER! What a finish by Cole Palmer. He equalises with a finish from about 22 yards out - low and hard beyond Unai Simon. Gareth Southgate punches the air. England are back in it!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Mikel Oyarzabal's left-footed shot from the right side of the box denied by Jordan Pickford.

real_commentary: Another substitute rides to England's rescue. A beautiful finish by Cole Palmer! He celebrated it with a trademark salute.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Midfield battle intensifies; England edges possession at 52.5%.

real_commentary: That goal has changed the momentum. England are enjoying their best spell of the final. All the noise is coming from England's fans. There is a new energy about the Three Lions now.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England asserting their dominance in midfield, controlling the tempo with 100% possession. Cole Palmer leading the charge with 9 key events.

real_commentary: 22 Premier League goals for Chelsea in 2023-24. One outstanding finish to rescue England in the Euro 2024 final. Take a bow, Cole Palmer.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession, controlling midfield for the last 2 minutes.

real_commentary: A massive chance for Spain! Lamine Yamal, who already has an assist, goes for glory from inside the box and it looks like it is going in before Jordan Pickford gets down to keep it out.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain dominating possession, controlling midfield for the last two minutes. 82.2% possession overall, led by Aymeric Laporte's activity.

real_commentary: This is agony! Spain have regained their composure after conceding an equaliser and now it's England who are hanging on.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Tactical change for Spain. Robin Le Normand makes way for José Iglesias.

real_commentary: A wonderful player. A wonderful finish.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Spain in firm control with 98.3% possession, dominating midfield.

real_commentary: Jordan Pickford is forced to come off his line and pluck a cross out of the air. Will England force extra time? Gareth Southgate is preparing more changes.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for Spain, delivered by Lamine Yamal. Declan Rice concedes.

real_commentary: Agony for England! Mikel Oyarzabal stretches to meet Marc Cucurella's low cross into the box and steer it past Jordan Pickford. Was he offside? No! England have four minutes plus stoppages to save this.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Spain 2, England 1. Mikel Oyarzabal Ugarte scores from the centre of the box, assisted by Marc Cucurella Saseta.

real_commentary: England need a hero. Ivan Toney is on for Phil Foden.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England dominating possession in midfield, showcasing 100% control. Ollie Watkins leading the charge with seven events.

real_commentary: SO CLOSE FOR ENGLAND! They win a corner and John Stones' header is somehow kept it. It falls to Declan Rice and the Marc Guehi. Spain somehow survive.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for Spain. Lamine Yamal makes way for Mikel Merino in a tactical switch.

real_commentary: Four minutes of additional time. 240 seconds for England to find another equaliser.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for England. Phil Foden off, Ivan Toney on.

real_commentary: Spain's substitutes are on the sidelines ready to celebrate.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Ollie Watkins (England) shown a yellow card for a foul on José Ignacio Fernández Iglesias (Spain).

real_commentary: A long clearance by Jordan Pickford and Bukayo Saka is onto it. The referee blows for a foul and Spain have a free-kick.
our_sequence_commentary: [Free Kick] Foul by Bukayo Saka (England) on Unai Simón (Spain). Free kick awarded in Spain's defensive half.

real_commentary: Spain win Euro 2024. England's long wait goes on.
our_sequence_commentary: [Free Kick] Free kick awarded to England after a foul by Mikel Merino on Marc Guehi.
